<sect2 id='gimp-prefs-default-grid'>
  <title lang='en'>Default Image Grid</title>
  <title lang='de'>Vorgabe-Bildgitter</title>
  <indexterm lang='en'>
    <primary>Dialogs</primary>
    <secondary>Preferences</secondary>
    <tertiary>Image grid</tertiary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm lang='de'>
    <primary>Dialoge</primary>
    <secondary>Einstellungen</secondary>
    <tertiary>Vorgabe-Gitter</tertiary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm lang='fr'>
    <primary></primary>
  </indexterm>

  <informalfigure>  
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject lang='en'>
        <imagedata fileref='../images/preferences/prefs-default-grid.png' format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject lang='de'>
        <imagedata fileref='../images/preferences/de/prefs-default-grid.png' format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject lang='fr'>
        <imagedata fileref='../images/preferences/fr/prefs-default-grid.png' format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
    <caption>
      <para lang='en'>
        Default Grid Preferences
      </para>
      <para lang='de'>
        Einstellungsdialog: Ansicht zum Vorgabe-Bildgitter
      </para>
    </caption>
  </informalfigure>  

  <para lang='de'>
    Diese Ansicht lässt Sie Standardeinstellungen des Bildgitters
    verändern.  Bette sehen Sie <link
    linkend='gimp-configure-grid-dialog'>Bildgitter</link>.
  </para>

  <para lang='en'>
    This page lets you customize the default properties of GIMP's grid,
    which can be toggled on or off using
    <menuchoice>
      <guimenu>View</guimenu>
      <guimenuitem>Show Grid</guimenuitem>
    </menuchoice>
    from the image menu.  The settings here match those in the
    Configure Image Grid dialog, which can be used to reconfigure the
    grid for an existing image, by choosing
    <menuchoice>
      <guimenu>Image</guimenu>
      <guimenuitem>Configure Grid</guimenuitem>
    </menuchoice>
    from the image menu.  See the <link
    linkend='gimp-configure-grid-dialog'>Configure Grid
    dialog</link> section for information on the meaning of each of
    the settings.
  </para>

</sect2>
